Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.app

Interface App

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppImpl
    public interface App
extends org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService

    The App client service represents the App that is calling the Tabris server. Sometimes its necessary to configure the App or to get notified when something happens within the App e.g. the App was sent to the background. The App provides facilities to accomplish these tasks.

    Since:
    0.10
    No Implement:
    This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients.

      • addEventListener

        void addEventListener​(EventType type,
                      AppListener listener)

        Registers an event listener that will be notified when an event of the specified EventType was fired within the App.

        Parameters:
        type - the EventType of interest
        listener - the listener that gets called when an event was fired within the App.
        See Also:
        AppListener

      • removeEventListener

        void removeEventListener​(EventType type,
                         AppListener listener)

        Removes an event listener.

      • addBackNavigationListener

        void addBackNavigationListener​(BackNavigationListener listener)

        On some devices a back navigation is possible using some kind of back button. When adding a BackNavigationListener the listener will be notified when the user presses the back button.

        See Also:
        BackNavigationListener

      • removeBackNavigationListener

        void removeBackNavigationListener​(BackNavigationListener listener)

        Removes a BackNavigationListener.

      • startInactivityTimer

        void startInactivityTimer​(int inactivityTime)

        With the addEventListener(EventType, AppListener) method you can register a listener for the EventType.INACTIVE. Inactive means a period with no user interactions. The startInactivityTimer(int) specifies the time that will be used to detect inactivity and starts the inactivity countdown.

        Parameters:
        inactivityTime - the inactivity time in ms.
        Since:
        1.1

      • stopInactivityTimer

        void stopInactivityTimer()

        Stops the inactivity countdown.

        Since:
        1.1

      • setScreenProtection

        void setScreenProtection​(boolean protect)

        Instructs the client to enable or disable screen protection. Each client can interpret screen protection differently e.g. showing a black screen.

        Since:
        1.1

      • hasScreenProtection

        boolean hasScreenProtection()

        Returns whether the screen is protected or not.

      • setBadgeNumber

        void setBadgeNumber​(int badgeNumber)

        Instructs the client to set the given number >= 0 as badge on the application icon. Set to {see SWT.NONE} to hide. Not all clients support badges on the application icon.

        Since:
        1.2
